#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_aac.rst:4
msgid ":index:`AAC Files <configuration; aac tag options>`"
msgstr ":index:`AAC-bestanden <configuratie; opties voor aac-tags>`"

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_aac.rst:6
msgid ""
"Picard can save APEv2 tags to pure AAC files, which by default do not "
"support tagging. APEv2 tags in AAC are supported by some players, but "
"players not supporting AAC files with APEv2 tags can have issues loading and "
"playing those files. To deal with this you can choose whether to save tags "
"to those files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_aac.rst:19
msgid "**Save APEv2 tags**"
msgstr "**APEv2-tags opslaan**"

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_aac.rst:21
msgid "Picard will save APEv2 tags to the files."
msgstr "Picard slaat APEv2-tags in de bestanden op."

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_aac.rst:23
msgid "**Do not save tags**"
msgstr "**Geen tags opslaan**"

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_aac.rst:25
msgid ""
"Picard will not save any tags to the files, but you can still use Picard to "
"rename them. By default existing APEv2 tags will be kept in the file."
msgstr ""
"Picard slaat geen tags in AAC-bestanden op, maar je kan Picard nog wel "
"gebruiken om die bestanden te hernoemen. Standaard worden bestaande APEv2-"
"tags behouden."

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_aac.rst:27
msgid "**Remove APEv2 tags**"
msgstr "**APEv2-tags verwijderen**"

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_aac.rst:29
msgid ""
"If you have \"Do not save tags\" enabled checking this option will cause "
"Picard to remove existing APEv2 tags from the file on saving."
msgstr ""
"Als je de optie ‘Geen tags opslaan’ hebt ingeschakeld en je deze optie "
"aanvinkt, verwijdert Picard bestaande APEv2-tags tijdens het opslaan uit de "
"bestanden."

#: ../../config/options_tags_compatibility_aac.rst:31
msgid ""
"Regardless of how you have configured saving tags Picard will always read "
"existing APEv2 tags in AAC files."
msgstr ""
"Hoe je deze opties ook hebt ingesteld, Picard zal bestaande APEv2-tags in "
"AAC-bestanden wel lezen."
